I start a new job coming up next week at a major defense contractor.  Bought some nice dress pants this evening, hoping to impress them with my brains and stunning looks so they make me management in a few years.  I'd love nothing more than to have my own team.

Very glad to be done with school.  Though getting that itch to go back.. don't you just hate that?

Roleplaying and mixed martial arts takes up alot of my time.  Information on music and movies taking a close second.  Though of course, my wonderful lady is of course number one on my mind.

Oh yeah, and I cut my hair... I miss it already.
http://darknessc.livejournal.com/3406.html

Many of you have heard of the story of me driving to Illinois on a road trip to see Kittie.  Recently started chatting with the owner of said destination.

May actually go try and she NiN in concert per her recommendation.  I've been reluctant to go back and see the new material.  I saw NiN twice in one week many years back and have been unsure if Trent could top that experience.

Been busy with school and work as per everyone else...  I blame pants.

Oh and drink mead, it makes you smart, funny, and wise.  I mean fuck the vikings drank at.
http://darknessc.livejournal.com/3072.html

Though I must admit its bad times, no where does it say in the Constitution or the Bill of Rights that citizens should receive natural disaster relief.  Plus the main problem was the local legislation of Louisana would not ask for aid.  The feds can't do anything prior to that due to this little thing call martial law.  Believe it or not the government can't deploy the national guard into your neighborhood willy nilly.

Furthermore, my default comment on all things natural diaster in the US: Theres a reason native americans where nomadic in that region.
http://darknessc.livejournal.com/2830.html

So... worst experience ever at work. Man thats owns a nearby gas station comes in with a laptop. Claims it doesn't print. Pull it out of the bag, remove the hard drive.... guess what?


Roaches come out.

Not like one either. The bag and the laptop where infested. Luckily my boss used to work for Orkin and still had some "toys" at home.



I wouldn't work on it.  I don't make nearly enough to put up with that.

anwser: Alex I believe the awnser to that is 6.


kids don't drive and run for the border.... its just to many modes of locomotion.

Hello everyone! After a brief hiatus I have returned. 


1. Moved into a new house recently. It's not to far from Josh's abode. Finally got the internet in my sinister grasp again! 

2. Been working at a little PC repair shop. 

3. Have you seen this years ozzfest lineup? Most of the bands I've been pimping are on it... I maybe forced to throwdown the big dollars and get backstage passes. Long live In Flames. 

4. Still single, I think? 

5. Sin City comes out friday... I will in fact see this movie. Probably more then once. 

6. It appears Johnnie Cochran just passed away at 67 from an inoperable brain tumor. 

8. The new nine inch nails single reminds me of kylie minogue. 

9. Patriot Center needs to rethink their ticket system. Please, when my ticket says doors at 7:30 and I show up at 7:06 and the band I came to see (shadowsfall by the way... and yes they on ozzfest this year main fucking stage) has been playing for awhile already, and they didn't even open, then theres a problem. 

I guess I'll stop there. I plead the Chewie defense.
http://darknessc.livejournal.com/1656.html

I just ate enough food that you couldn't pay me to eat more. Had to help people find a hair dryer earlier to fill an air mattress.

This years holiday swag was better then last year. Well last year I got a salad bowl. Got more penguin paraphernalia in the form of a coffee mug, hand towels, and 2 ornaments. Received two music video DVD's, monte cook's Arcane Unearthed, and some socks of course.

Almost had nothing put a cordless combo toolkit... Had to bring up that I would not be able to find much use for a chainsaw that wasn't larcenic in intent.

Well kids I hope everyone is having a good time with friends and/or family, or just getting snuggly with their someone special.
